Root project README. Documents purpose, layout, generated tool contracts (four binaries: `ctx-context`, `ctx-verify`, `ctx-scan`, `ctx-cage`), and a generated architecture overview.

Two blocks between `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED ... -->` / `<!-- END GENERATED ... -->` markers are machine-written and checked for drift by `ctx-verify` (`contracts` and `architecture` checks respectively) — never hand-edit inside them. The tool-contracts block is regenerated by `scripts/gen_tool_contracts.sh --write` from each binary's own `--contract` output; the architecture block by `scripts/gen_readme_architecture.sh --write` from the repo root's generated rollup in `.context/`. Editing this file means either touching prose outside the markers freely, or re-running the corresponding generator script after changing the source of truth (binary `--contract` impls or `.context/` rollups) — manual edits inside markers will be silently overwritten and then flagged as drift by CI.

References `../meal-planning/` as an external reference project, not part of this repo; its own README is the entry point for that consumer workspace. Points to `.context/intent.md` (doctrine), `docs/DECISIONS.md` (rationale), and `docs/STATUS.md` (current work) as the authoritative non-generated docs — this file doesn't duplicate their content.